Privacy Policy
At EivaaGames, we take the private nature of your information very seriously. This policy regarding our privacy practices (the "Privacy Policy") describes how we treat the information we collect when you visit and use eivaagames.com (the "Site") and/or any of our mobile apps/games. When you use the Services, you also consent to the collection, transfer, manipulation, storage, disclosure and other uses of your information as described in this Privacy Policy; please read it carefully.
What information do we gather and track?
We do not directly gather any personally identifiable information about your visit to our website or while using our mobile apps. But the services we use for advertisements may collect some data regarding your usage of the service (see the Advertisements section below).
If you:
● Sign up for a free member account.
● Download a trial version of our software.
● Sign onto a page that requires authorization...
You may be asked to provide us your username and email address. We may use the information you provide to:
● Keep you informed of new releases of our products.
● Provide helpful hints and tips on how to use our products.
● Make special offers that we extend only to our registered customers.
● Improve our site and the services we offer you.
In some of our apps, you may be asked to enter the username or player name, this name is stored locally on your device and is submitted to the online leader-boards if you are among the top players, if you are out of the top players then your username or player name is removed from the online server. If you wish your username or player name to be removed from the online leader-boards while you are among the top players then please
contact us
.
We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13, allow them to sign up for newsletters or make purchases. EivaaGames takes privacy of children seriously and encourages parents to play an active role in their children’s online experience at all times. We urge parents to instruct their children never to give out their real names, addresses, or phone numbers, without parental permission, when online.
Our apps use third party services that may collect information used to identify you.
